data.text:
Kent State University Communications and Marketing records

Finding Aid

Prepared by Gail Redmann, December 15, 1993; Prepared for the Web by Barbara Bass, July 19, 1996; Last updated: November 2022

Inclusive Dates: 1938-2022

Bulk Dates: 1965-1991

Extent: 82 cubic feet (82 record storage boxes)

Physical Location: 11th floor

Scope and Content: This collection contains records transferred from News and Information Services (now University Communications and Marketing) to University Archives. Included are personnel clippings files which usually contain press releases and basic biographical information on KSU faculty and staff. The second major portion of the collection is comprised of subject files related to various campus events, organizations, people, and places. The third section of the collection contains official press releases on a wide range of KSU-related events, people, and news items, arranged in chronological order. The bulk of the collection dates from 1965-1980. Updates will be made in the future when additional records from this office are processed.

Arrangement: The collection is organized into the following three series of records.

Series 1: Personnel Clippings

Series 2: Subject Files

Series 3: Press Releases

Series 1: Personnel Clippings

Arrangement: The Personnel Clippings are organized alphabetically by surname and are filed in unnumbered boxes. Please request these files by the name(s) of person(s) whose clippings you wish to view.
